<item>
            <title>[LU-18403] Add ldlm.namespaces.*.enable_dynamic_lru parameter</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-18403</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Originally, LDLM always had a static LRU size defined by the &lt;tt&gt;lru_size&lt;/tt&gt; parameter. When dynamic LRU sizing was implemented, setting &quot;lru_size=0&quot; was taken as &quot;change to dynamic LRU sizing&quot;. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;For historic reasons, reading from the &lt;tt&gt;ldlm.namespaces.&amp;#42;.lru_size&lt;/tt&gt; parameter returns the number of locks currently in the LRU for that lock namespace. This usage to fetch the current lock count was replaced long ago by the &quot;&lt;tt&gt;...lock_count&lt;/tt&gt;&quot; parameter (similar to the &quot;resource_count parameter, unless there are multiple DLM locks on a single object (eg. read locks, non-overlapping write locks, etc.).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Any usage of &quot;&lt;tt&gt;lru_size&lt;/tt&gt;&quot; in the test scripts to get the current lock count should be replaced by &quot;&lt;tt&gt;lock_count&lt;/tt&gt;&quot;.  A second patch should be made to return the actual setting of &lt;tt&gt;lru_size&lt;/tt&gt; (including zero), not the current lock count in case of dynamic LRU size. &lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="85471">LU-18403</key>
